#A62A2A>(3/25/02 7:26:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What magical gloves ?</span><hr size=1> Gnome skin gloves would be nice, though that's high level.  Lower level, you can carry around lightstones in your hands, and punch with those... that will count.  Wu's fighing gauntlets can be tailored, and these would help a lot.<br><br>Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 416<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/25/02 12:47:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What magical gloves ?</span><hr size=1> Go to Warsliks when someone camps the forts for the destroyer, I let about 20 pairs of gloves rot since there is never anyone there to take them off the corpse and they are lore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 232<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/25/02 2:11:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What magical gloves ?</span><hr size=1> What are you fighting that you need magic gloves ?<br><br>If you're planning on whisp hunting, take a spin killing frogloks in the swamp or upper guk, netted/mesh is magical. If you're going to hunt whisps on whisp isle there are also frog's in the sewers of Qeynos.<br><br>the Warslick thing would also be good if someone is hunting Grinny, you could also prolly pick up a stack of loot from the corpses. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udhalillama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dhali Llama</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepage.eircom.net/~bray/pp/vgstarry.jpg " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/20/02 12:36:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What magical gloves ?</span><hr size=1>  &quot;Lower level, you can carry around lightstones in your hands, and punch with those... that will count&quot;<br><br>This doesnt work.  When a Monk holds anything cept weapons in his hands (lightstones, fire beetle eyes, ect), he doesn't attack...except for 'special' attacks (kick, round kick, tiger claw, ect).<br><br>This may have worked in the past, but it no longer does.<br>As far as your question bout low level magic stuff, Qeynos Catacombs and Innothule Swamp, as mentioned above, froglocks drop netted stuff pretty regular.  Also in the Warrens you can get Pit Fighter's hand and ankle wraps, the mob is around level 10-12 I beleive that drops the Pit Fighter wraps.<br>Frogs in Qeynos Catacombs are a little higher level than most in the swamp.  If I remember correctly, the swamp frogs are around levels 5-7?  While the Qeynos versions are about 7-9.<br><br>Dhali Llama <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.show